Remove from src/openhuman/mod.rs and src/core/all.rs.

### 1.4  src/openhuman/socket/   (~6 files, ~1,550 LOC)
The entire Socket.IO WebSocket connection to wss://api.tinyhumans.ai/socket.io.
This is the transport that delivered ChannelInboundMessage events to channels/bus.rs.
Once deleted, channels/bus.rs has no feeder and can be deleted too (Section 1.5).

Pre-deletion: move `WebhookRouter` out of `SocketManager::shared.webhook_router`.
The router currently lives here because the backend socket manager held a reference to it.
After the move, store it in a standalone global in src/openhuman/webhooks/ (a OnceLock
or similar), and update global_socket_manager().webhook_router() callers to use the
new accessor.

Files to delete once WebhookRouter is moved:
  - src/openhuman/socket/mod.rs
  - src/openhuman/socket/manager.rs         (SocketManager, global accessor, SharedState)
  - src/openhuman/socket/ws_loop.rs         (Engine.IO/Socket.IO WebSocket loop, ~680 LOC)
  - src/openhuman/socket/event_handlers.rs  (parse_sio_event, handle_sio_event, ~490 LOC)
  - src/openhuman/socket/types.rs
  - src/openhuman/socket/schemas.rs         (socket RPC schema registrations)

Also delete src/api/socket.rs (websocket_url builder only used by ws_loop).
Remove socket module from src/openhuman/mod.rs.
Remove SocketManager startup from src/core/jsonrpc.rs.

### 1.5  src/openhuman/channels/bus.rs   (+ bus_tests.rs if present)
The ChannelInboundSubscriber subscribes to DomainEvent::ChannelInboundMessage events
emitted by the backend socket. All outbound operations (send_channel_reply,
send_typing_indicator, send_filler_message, delete_channel_message, progressive edits)
