### 1.10  src/openhuman/tools/impl/network/web_search.rs
WebSearchTool routes search through the backend's Parallel integration proxy.
With IntegrationClient gone this file is dead.

Options (choose one):
  a) Wire a direct search API (Brave Search API, SerpAPI, or Tavily) behind a user-configured
     API key. Simplest: Brave's `https://api.search.brave.com/res/v1/web/search` requires
     only a `X-Subscription-Token` header and returns JSON. Add `brave_search_api_key` to
     the config and route through that when present.
  b) Remove the tool entirely and deregister it from the orchestrator tools list.

Do NOT leave a stub that silently returns empty results. If option (b) is chosen,
remove the `web_search` / `gitbooks_search` tool registrations from
src/openhuman/tools/orchestrator_tools.rs.

