  app/test/e2e/specs/auth-access-control.spec.ts
    Tests backend-auth gating (ProtectedRoute behaviour with/without token). In the fork
    there is no app-login so the gating concept is different. Remove or replace with a
    test that verifies the native OAuth grant flow enables features.

  app/test/e2e/specs/gmail-flow.spec.ts
  app/test/e2e/specs/notion-flow.spec.ts
  app/test/e2e/specs/telegram-flow.spec.ts
    These test Composio-backed integrations that required a backend session to authorize.
    In direct Composio mode (fork default) or native OAuth, the flows differ.
    Audit each: if the spec drives a flow that now works natively, rewrite it;
    if the spec depends on backend auth scaffolding that no longer exists, remove it.

  app/test/e2e/specs/channels-smoke.spec.ts
    Check whether this tests the backend-relayed channel path or the native channel
    runtime. If it tests login + channel connectivity via the backend, remove; if it
    tests the native runtime, keep and update any backend setup steps.

### 7.2  Unit tests — go with their modules
Deleted Rust modules (billing, referral, team, socket, bus, openhuman_backend, etc.)
carry their own test modules. They are deleted with the module.

### 7.3  Mock server
scripts/mock-api-core.mjs / scripts/mock-api-server.mjs stub the backend for Rust
integration tests (json_rpc_e2e.rs uses it). Once backend-calling RPC methods are
removed from all.rs, the mock server stubs for those methods can be removed.
The mock server itself may still be useful for Composio direct-mode mocking — keep the
framework, remove the backend-specific stubs (auth, billing, team, referral routes).

### 7.4  tests/json_rpc_e2e.rs
Remove:
  - invoke_auth_store_session_missing_token_fails_validation test
  - Any test that calls billing / team / referral RPC methods
  - Any assertion against "no backend session token" error strings
  - The BACKEND_URL env var setup helper if it only serves removed tests

